node.text:
I’m so happy to be the winner of the wrecks category in @upycontest 2025 I also got a 3rd place and one highly commended image in the wrecks category. 

Winning image is the Gulf fleet No.31 wreck that sits at 104m depth in the Red Sea. 

3rd place is the SG115 coast guard ship that sits at 30m depth in Kaş, Türkiye. 

Highly commended image is the SS Carthage that sits at  84m depth near Çanakkale, Türkiye.
Thank you so much @bollerup_gonediving for your kind words 🥳🤩🥳
Massive congratulations with the well deserved recognition! Your artwork and storytelling through photography is incredible!
You can do it @freediveanna you can see the wreck from 70m 😅🤣🤣
ok it‘s a bit deep for freediving 😂
Wow you are always an inspiration👏🏽
Quanto sei bravo a trovare questi reperti super bravo 😍😍😍😍😍😍😍
Well done Alex and our little Bodrum wreck looks amazing.Congrats
Congrats for your wins. Amazing photos as always👌🤿🤙
👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️After all, the underwater world is amazing ❤️
Well deserved and excellent work as always. Super inspiring 👏👏🔥🔥❤️
Consistently producing the most beautiful and awesome images from the deep blue They really inspires to go there and see for yourself 🔥
